The Nigerian Army engaged Boko Haram terrorists in fierce battle in Borno State, killing many and rescuing some kidnapped victims.  The Headquarters of the Nigerian Army in Abuja, in a tweet @HQNigerianArmy wrote: “Ongoing offensive onslaught by troops of Operation Desert Sanity records another feat as troops neutralized several ISWAP/BokoHaram terrorists around Ndufu and Musiri villages in Borno State. Also, troops recovered weapons and rescued 30 kidnapped local residents.”

The Army added: @HQNigerianArmy “Additionally, troops also destroyed various camps of the terrorists.”

